CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 9, 1945, pg. 13 reads: "On The Top Rung - Not only in [sic] Vernalyn White of Chauncey Street sitting on the top rung of the fence, she is also at the top of her class at Schenley High School, being an "A" Grade student all the way down the line. She likes sports, especially bowling.  Looks and brains are a good combination in this instance. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Vernalyn White, seated on fence rail with A. Leo Weil Elementary School on Centre Avenue in background
